  "text": "LiCl was found to be essential for the formation of heatinduced gels, but the question whether compounds other than LiCl can be effective in forming heat-induced emulsion gels remains to be answered. We demonstrated that heat-induced gels can also be prepared using HCl, and the sol-gel transition temperatures also decrease linearly with increasing C18AA concentration [CITATION_1] . Interestingly, the solgel transition of the O/W emulsions was also very sensitive to pH, and it was possible to reversibly control the sol-gel phase transition by changing the pH over many cycles [CITATION_2] .",
